A real-time AI-powered SQL activity dashboard that detects database changes, explains them using local Llama AI, and alerts you about anomalies â€” all free and open-source.



ğŸ“Œ Project: AI-Powered Real-Time SQL Change Analyzer Dashboard
ğŸ“– Overview

I want to build a real-time SQL activity monitoring dashboard that automatically:

detects inserts, updates, deletes happening inside any MySQL database

highlights changes visually in a dashboard

explains changes using AI (free, local model like Llama 3 in Ollama)

identifies anomalies, strange patterns, or suspicious updates

acts like a â€œsmart DB inspectorâ€ for developers and teams

It should work like a mini real-time SQL Copilot, fully open-source, free to use, and anyone should be able to connect their own MySQL database easily.

ğŸ§© Core Idea

The system listens to binlog events in MySQL (binary log), which contain:

what changed

which table

before/after values

timestamp

These change events are streamed into the UI using WebSockets.

AI analyzes each change and produces:

human-friendly explanations

anomaly detection

â€œwhat might have caused this?â€ suggestions

â€œis this risky?â€ classification

