Any MySQL instance (user chooses)

User enters credentials through a UI settings page

No database access from frontend â€” backend only.

ğŸ”’ Why Backend Connection Is Required

Frontend cannot connect to SQL directly.

So:
Frontend â†’ Backend â†’ User MySQL

The dashboard will allow the user to input:

host

port

user

password

database

Backend dynamically connects and restarts binlog listener.

ğŸ§  AI Logic

When the backend receives a binlog event:

Convert raw event into a structured JSON diff:

table name

action type

old values

new values

timestamp

Send the data into Llama 3 (via Ollama):

â€œExplain this changeâ€

â€œIs this normal?â€

â€œWhat might this mean?â€

â€œIs this an anomaly?â€

Return AI explanation to frontend.

ğŸš€ How the Dashboard Works
1. User connects their database

They open Settings â†’ Database Configuration and enter details.

Backend saves config and reconnects automatically.

2. Backend starts MySQL binlog listener

It listens to:

INSERT

UPDATE

DELETE

Metadata changes

Every event is processed immediately.

3. Backend streams changes to frontend

Using WebSockets:

{ 
  type: "UPDATE",
  table: "users",
  before: { name: "John" },
  after: { name: "Johnny" },
  at: "2025-01-15T10:22:31"
}

4. AI analyzes each change

Local model explains the update in simple language:

"The user 'John' updated their name to 'Johnny'. 
Likely a user profile change. Not suspicious."


Or

"3000 rows deleted from 'orders'. 
Unusual operation. Possibly bulk cleanup or accidental query."

5. Frontend displays the event

UI shows:

highlighted updated row

animation for new events

AI insights in a side panel

timeline of changes

table-specific activity

6. Dashboard Features
âœ” Real-Time Activity Stream

Sidebar showing all events streaming live.

âœ” Table Activity Heatmap

Which table is being modified most?

âœ” AI Explanations

Local Llama explains each event.

âœ” Anomaly Alerts

AI marks unusual queries:

too many deletes

SQL pattern anomalies

high-frequency writes

repeated updates in same table

âœ” Timeline Viz

A visual timeline of changes.

âœ” Diff Viewer UI

Compare before/after values in a pretty diff format.

